post_text:
Though we must limit spectators to live athletic events due to the Governor’s guidelines, we are EXCITED to be able to bring lots of FALCON SPORTS excitement directly to your laptop or mobile device!

This week, the Golf match at Fairview Golf Course, will be Live Streamed from the 18th hole, Wednesday, Sept. 16, at approximately 3:30 PM on CCHStoday.com. Our senior golfers will be recognized.

There is NO Admission fee for viewing live streamed CCHS sports events, so be sure to bookmark CCHStoday.com and return Friday, Sept. 18 for the first Home Cedar Crest football game at 7 PM! (Log on at 6:30 PM for the senior football player recognition night event before the game!)

#FalconPride!

Parents/Guardians are invited to attend a VIRTUAL OPEN HOUSE tonight (Thursday, Sept. 10, 2020) in their child’s elementary school! This is an exciting evening for students and parents to safely meet their child’s teachers and other staff members in a virtual environment and gain additional insights into the educational programming and building information for the 2020-2021 school year.

Look in your Skyward Message Center for the complete schedule for the evening and links to your child’s principal and classroom teacher presentations during each visitation period.

This is for parents/guardians who signed up on the survey for students who are enrolled 100% in a virtual learning option (K-8 Virtual or C3) ... This pickup is NOT for students who are in the CLSD Blue & Gray Hybrid learning option. Hybrid students can pick up their meals at the end of their in-person school day.

TODAY (Monday, Aug. 31) is the first weekly meals pick-up for families who ordered meals between last Friday and today at 3 PM.

This meals program is for any CLSD student who is enrolled in our fully virtual learning options (CLSD K-8 and Cedar Crest Cyber)!

Meal packages will be charged according to each family's free, reduced or paid meals status. For more details and to pre-order for the first week's meals pick up (TODAY), click here and scroll down to the Virtual Solutions Menu: https://www.clsd.k12.pa.us/clsd-home/departments/food-services/

Meal packages contain 5 breakfasts and 5 lunches for the week. This first week's entrees include chicken tenders, pizza, hamburger and grilled cheese; plus half-gallon of milk and PLENTY of fruits and vegetables (see image, below)!

School starts Monday, August 31, 2020, and our Food Service staff is ready to safely provide delicious, healthy meals to all CLSD students enrolled in all of our learning options!

Breakfast and lunch menus for students in Elementary (K-5), CCMS and CCHS are available on the CLSD website now: https://www.clsd.k12.pa.us/clsd-home/departments/food-services/lunch-breakfast-menus/. A special 5-day breakfast and lunch pick-up menu for students in the CLSD K-8 and C3 virtual learning programs will be posted soon!

More information regarding free and reduced price meals, ordering details for students in the Blue/Gray hybrid learning option to take home meals for online learning days ... and so much more will be available Friday!

Families participating in the K-8 Virtual and C3 programs, should expect to receive information regarding meal distribution directly to their Skyward Message Center and email.

post_text: Thursday, July 30, is the last distribution day of the summer for the CLSD Grab ’n Go meals program! Free DOUBLE meals to ALL children from 8-9:15 AM and from 11AM-12:14 PM ONLY at Cedar Crest Middle School. Double meals, muffin meals available; milk in quarts.
text: Thursday, July 30, is the last distribution day of the summer for the CLSD Grab ’n Go meals program! Free DOUBLE meals to ALL children from 8-9:15 AM and from 11AM-12:14 PM ONLY at Cedar Crest Middle School. Double meals, muffin meals available; milk in quarts.

post_text:
TIME FOR LUNCH!!! Today (7-22-2020) is a double meals day!

The CLSD Grab ’n Go meals program is distributing Free DOUBLE meals to ALL children from 8-9:15 AM and 11AM-12:14 PM ONLY at Cedar Crest Middle School on Mondays, Wednesdays and Thursdays. The last day of distribution will be July 30, 2020.

On July 30th, all participants will receive the last double meal of the summer which will contain meals for both Friday (July 31st) and Saturday (August 1st). CLSD Food Service thanks all the families who participated in the program, as you all are the reason why we have continued serving through the month of July. We are extremely proud to serve this community.

post_text:
IMPORTANT CHANGES To Free Meals Distribution Sites and Times through the end of June 2020!

Wednesday, June 24, 2020, through Monday, June 29, 2020: Meals will be distributed ONLY on these three dates and ALL MEALS WILL BE DOUBLE MEALS to help families for two days at a time.
>Wednesday, June 24
>Thursday, June 25
>Monday, June 29
NO Meals distribution: Friday, June 26, or Tuesday, June 30.

The same meals are available at all three sites, at these NEW times:
NEW TIME-> 8:15-11:45 AM – Union Canal Elem
NEW TIME-> 8-9:30 AM – Church of the Good Shepherd
NEW LOCATION-> 11:00 AM to 12:30 PM – Ebenezer Elementary School, 1600 Colonial Circle, Lebanon, PA 17046

Two free breakfasts & two free lunches per child. Child(ren) must be present to receive meals. Children may walk to the sites (if there is a safe path). Meals must be consumed off site.

post_text: Shawn Small represented CLSD in today's national webinar hosted by the National Association of Music Merchants (NAMM). The District has been honored with the Best Communities for Music Education designation from the NAMM Foundation for its outstanding commitment to music education for five consecutive years. It joins 754 districts across the country in receiving the prestigious award.The award program recognizes outstanding efforts by teachers, administrators, parents, students and community leaders who have made music education part of a well-rounded education. Designations are made to districts and schools that demonstrate an exceptionally high commitment and access to music education.

Today, May 6, 2020, is National School Nurse Appreciation Day! The theme this year – "School Nurses: Supporting Students in Times of Crisis" – reinforces the changing times of 2020 and reflects the significant roles school nurses have in the health care of their school communities to help make a healthier place for children and families to learn and grow during this crisis.

To all of the nurses in our school buildings and those who assist on field trips, we thank you for all you do for our students and staff!

post_text:
A huge shout-out to Senator Dave Arnold who was among the volunteer readers who visited Ebenezer Elementary School today. Senator Arnold read to first grade students in Mrs. Neiswender's classroom.

His visit was coordinated by the United Way of Lebanon County and Visit Lebanon Valley who teamed to celebrate “Read Across America” and promote early literacy throughout Lebanon County this week.

Senator Arnold read the newly released book, “The Adventures of Lebanon Lilly.” Written and illustrated by Lebanon County natives Jennifer Kuzo and M.J. McFalls, the book tells the story of an adventurous cow named Lilly who leaves her pasture to explore her hometown. Lilly finds some great local treasures, including the Lebanon Valley Rail Trail, Cornwall Iron Furnace, Memorial Lake and Union Canal Tunnel Park!

CCHS will dismiss at 1:30 PM; CCMS will dismiss at 2 PM. All elementary schools will dismiss at the normal time.

We appreciate everyone's cooperation with the unusual circumstances affecting this school day.

Cornwall-Lebanon School District is updating its Alumni Directory of graduates of Cedar Crest, Cornwall, and South Lebanon high schools.

If you receive a postcard or email from Dr. Domencic, or a phone call from a representative of PCI (Publishing Concepts), it is legitimate! Thank you for participating by calling the 800# to verify or update your alumni information for our records.

If you did not receive a postcard or an email, you may call either of these numbers to update your information: 1-800-242-3706 or 1-800-249-5235. You do NOT need to know your personal I.D. number; they can look up your information by your name.

Yes, you will be asked if you'd like to purchase a directory, but you are under NO OBLIGATION to do so.

Please read the article on the District Home page for more information: www.clsd.k12.pa.us

Cornwall-Lebanon School District added 7 new photos.
January 29 at 5:33 PM ·

Congratulations to Andrew Ney for earning the title of Ebenezer Elementary School’s 2020 National Geographic GeoBee School Champion!

Sophia Vuong claimed 2nd place and Sammy Zeisloft earned 3rd place honors. All three students are in fifth grade. A total of eighteen students in fourth and fifth grade scored high enough on the qualifying test to earn the right to compete in the GeoBee.

The winning question was:
"The saola, an animal often called the Asian Unicorn, can be found in the Annan Cordillera of Vietnam and what neighboring landlocked country?"
Answer: "Laos"

The National Geographic GeoBee is an annual competition designed to inspire and reward students' curiosity about the world.

Andrew said he’ll start studying tonight to take the online State Qualifying test before the February 7 deadline! State GeoBee qualifiers will be announced on March 2, 2020.

Each year, a small group of senior boys at Cedar Crest High School are nominated by their classmates for the honor of participating in this Student Council sponsored fundraiser. They do this by carrying creatively decorated cans and asking for donations for the American Heart Association from friends and businesses over the course of a month. The student who raises the most money is crowned at the King of Hearts Dance in the CCHS cafe on February 7, 2020.

In past years, CCHS students and the community have proven to be extremely generous for this cause. Last year, they exceeded their goal and raised $32,000.

This year’s goal is $40,000!

Members of the 2020 King of Hearts court are John Fitzgibbons, Jonas Funk, Eric Wawrzyniak, Jack Beasley, Cade Rambler, Brady Miller, Jason Eberhart, Dylan Tull, Cole Miller, Chris Byler, Owen Kreider, Anthony Tornetta.

post_text: Almost 90 Union Canal ES 5th grade students participated in the 2019 D.A.R.E program graduation ceremony, held in the building's new LGI room.
text: Almost 90 Union Canal ES 5th grade students participated in the 2019 D.A.R.E program graduation ceremony, held in the building's new LGI room.

shared_text:
Cornwall-Lebanon School District added 13 new photos.
December 12, 2019 at 7:20 PM ·

Thank you to North Lebanon Township Police Department and Sgt. Duane Koons for your time, commitment, and dedication to the Union Canal D.A.R.E. program this fall! Through this community partnership, almost 90 fifth-grade students benefited from nine hours of direct instruction with a NLT officer, as well as multiple lessons, concepts, and discussions that took place daily, both formally and informally.

D.A.R.E. is a decision making model that stands for Define, Assess, Respond, and Evaluate. The core instruction addresses skills and abilities to resist drugs and violence, but the program model teaches students much more: how to make positive decisions as they grow into the person they want to be and become a valuable member of our community.

Principal McGinty, Chief Easter and officers from NLT, PA State Police and CLSD Officer Werner congratulated each student at today’s graduation program held in the new LGI room at UC.

Cedar Crest High School Student Council is partnering with each of the third grade classrooms in the District for Connecting Over Literature and Art (COLA). Student Council students developed the program with Dr. Clemens and their advisor Mrs. Hepler after attending the Principal-Advisor–Leaders (PAL) Conference at #LVC this fall.

Congratulations to the state qualifying cross country athletes recognized at the November Board meeting: Gwyneth Young, Shayla Bonzelet, Luke Hinegardner, Ryan Wolfe, Tommy Bildheiser, William Sheffield, Ryan Scicchitano (in absentia), Ben McElroy, and Dominique Smith-Rodriguez!

In presenting the athletes, Coach Brandon Risser shared that the boys team turned in the best finish in the 40-yr history of CCXC!

Coach Risser also noted that this is the third year for junior Gwyneth Young to be recognized as a state qualifier in XC and the first for senior Shayla Bonzelet (who has qualified for states in Track & Field since her freshman year). Young set a new school record this year: 17:54!

shared_text:
American Heart Association - Lebanon, PA Division
October 23, 2019 at 10:20 AM ·

Amazing things happen when you put your heart into them. That's why we were honored to present the Young Heart Award to Tyler Reinhart, a 6th grader at Cedar Crest Middle School, Cornwall-Lebanon School District, for his outstanding work raising funds and awareness for the American Heart Association. He raised more than $10,200 while participating in our Kids Heart Challenge programs at Ebenezer Elementary School over the past 6 years, helping his school earn a spot among the top 10 fundraising schools in the nation! Congratulations and a heartfelt THANK YOU to Tyler! #KidsHeartChallenge

Congratulations to the Cornwall Elementary and Cedar Crest High School Odyssey of the Mind teams! Both were recognized at the May School Board meeting for qualifying at their state level balsa wood events to compete at the Odyssey of the Mind World Finals.

At the Worlds event at Michigan State University, the Cornwall team earned 3rd place out of 52 other teams in their category. The CCHS team earned 2nd place out of 53 other teams in their category.

Odyssey of the Mind teams are tasked with developing creative solutions to original problems. The teams begin meeting in the fall to prepare for the late spring competitions.

Read more about the teams in the Lebanon Daily News: https://www.ldnews.com/story/news/education/2019/06/04/cornwall-lebanon-pa-world-odyssey-mind-finals-school/1327406001/ ... and on LebTown.com

post_text:
#FalconPride! Kudos to CCMS Principal Mariah Rackley, who has been enjoying a great year as one of three National Association of Secondary Principals (NASSP) Digital Principals of the Year, culminating in a cover photo and feature article in the current issue of the professional organization's magazine.

As a Digital Principal of the Year, Mrs. Rackley shared her knowledge of how to use technology to advance education and community connections by hosting national Twitter chats, writing national blog posts, speaking and presenting at regional and national conferences, completing a national Leadership Endorsement program, and serving as keynote speaker at the recent P4CE (Partners for Connecting Educators) Conference in Cape May.

Click here to watch the CCHS Today interview with Mrs. Rackley: https://youtu.be/oOU1VHkNeHs

post_text: Challenge Day 2019 turned out to be a beautiful day to be in the CCHS stadium! Each year, students in National Honor Society invite students from the life skills and multiple disabilities classes at CCHS and CCMS to participate in a fun-filled field day. NHS students serve as "buddies," and together the students enjoy relay races, softball throws, face painting, "Simon Says" games, as well as other activities and socializing. In the LGI inside, students enjoy quieter games together with their buddies. Everyone brings a picnic lunch and everyone is a winner!

In the 22 years that Mr. Rob Bare has been championing these activities at Ebenezer Elementary School, the students have raised almost $640,000 for #AHA! Congratulations! #FalconPride!
American Heart Association - Lebanon, PA Division

Amy Wissinger
February 15, 2019 at 10:42 AM ·

post_text: The Cedar Crest girls basketball team presented the Lebanon chapter of the American Cancer Society with a check for $2,703 generated from its Foul Shots for Cancer initiative prior to Friday's game. Through Foul Shots for Cancer, each player pledges to shoot 500 foul shots throughout the season, either before, during or after practice and to secure sponsors to aid in the fundraising. The girls’ efforts have resulted in donations exceeding $21,000 for the ACS over the past seven years. #FalconPride! #FalconsCare!

PENNLIVE.COM
How NBA referee Ashley Moyer-Gleich dealt with F-bombs and B-words to earn respect in a man's world

PennLive.com
January 6, 2019 at 3:25 PM ·

Camp Hill resident Ashley Moyer-Gleich is in her second month as the fourth-ever female NBA referee. The former Cedar Crest and Millersville guard wasn't planning to be a ref at all but a college coach. Now she laughs in amazement at how quickly it's all happened. At just 31, she's become the fastest-rising young official in the game's modern history.

Sunday, Jan. 6, 2019, 2 p.m., is the CCHS Winter Band Pops Concert! The program will feature light, popular works including a West Side Story medley in honor of what would have been Leonard Bernstein’s 100th birthday, and a compilation of songs from the rock band, Chicago. And, who doesn’t love a good polka?! Additional works by Grundman, Bagley, LaPlante, and Sousa will be performed. Mr. Scott Muenz is Director of CCHS Bands.

Tickets are $3 general admission are available by calling 272-2033, ext. 5106; or, at the CCHS Auditorium door, prior to the performance. CLSD Gold cards will be accepted; No reservation needed.

post_text:
Kudos to the CCHS Battle Buddies Club and advisor Stephen Thompson for brightening the day of many veterans this holiday season. Students from throughout the District made 653 holiday cards that were distributed to veterans. Battle Buddies members greeted veterans and their families at the Lebanon VA complex with refreshments, smiles, and a holiday card made by a student.

They also sent more than 200 cards to recovering veterans at Walter Reed Army Medical Center in Northwest Washington D.C.

Kudos to the students and their advisor for coordinating this meaningful and heartfelt project!

post_text: Cedar Crest High School Student Council officers Emily Yoder, Cyja Hepler and Ella Longenecker hold the PA State Student Conference gavel with ribbons from all host schools over the years. CCHS is hosting the 2018 Conference, November 8-10, 2018. Cyja also serves as PA Student Council President. Eleven hundred student council members from 100 schools across PA and Delaware are registered to participate in three days of workshops, leadership activities and sessions with motivational speakers. A dance and check presentation to the state student council charity (Children's Miracle Network) will conclude the conference.

post_text: Breakfast has taken off at #CCMS! The Grab 'n Go Breakfast cart is a hit every morning as an average of 126 students stop by the Commons area to grab a healthy breakfast. Research shows that student behavior, mental health, academic success, physical health, attendance, and punctuality are improved when students start their day with a nutritious breakfast. Thanks to Governor Tom Wolf and Pennsylvania Department of Education for providing a mini grant/School Breakfast Initiative to enable the purchase of the portable serving carts to provide an easy alternative breakfast option!

Research shows that student behavior, mental health, academic success, physical health, attendance, and punctuality are improved when students start their day with a nutritious breakfast. Thanks to Governor Tom Wolf and Pennsylvania Department of Education for providing a mini grant/School Breakfast Initiative to enable the purchase of the portable serving carts to provide an easy alternative breakfast option!

post_text: These CCHS students, along with other area high school students, participated in the Youth Civic Engagement Symposium held at LVC. Developed by Senator Pat Toomey’s office in honor of Constitution Day (Sept. 14), its goal was to help high school students better understand the legislative, executive and judicial branches of federal, state and local government. The symposium also explored careers in government and encouraged students to become more aware and involved in the civic arena.

post_text:
#FalconPride! Congratulations to Mike Webster CCHS '08, who won 1st place in the Transit Division at the recent state competition for PA School Bus Drivers! Mike is a substitute driver at Brightbill Transportation for both CLSD and ELCO. Best wishes as he represents the team at Nationals on July 22.

Kudos, too, to Brightbill Transportation's team of drivers for winning 2nd place in the overall team competition! The competition is for all drivers who qualified to represent IU13 on a 10-man team. The IU13 team was an all-Brightbill Transportation team of drivers from CLSD and other districts they service. It's a highly competitive event that includes written and multiple skills tests that encompass all aspects of driving a school bus.

Due to the inclement weather, graduation for the CCHS Class of 2018 will be held inside the new gym tonight, Thursday, May 31, 2018. Admission will be for those with gray tickets only. Everyone, including young children and babies, must have a gray ticket for entrance to the gym. For those who do not have a gray ticket, the CCHS Auditorium will be open and the event will be Live-streamed to the screen there.

In addition, the Live stream of tonight’s Commencement ceremony can be viewed, beginning at about 5:45 PM, here: http://www.cchstoday.com or, directly from the cchstoday Youtube stream here: https://youtu.be/uFqgM7436iI

post_text:
The Cedar Crest HS Orchestra will perform its annual spring concert Tuesday, May 15, 7:30 p.m. at the Cedar Crest High School Auditorium.

Admission is free and open to the public. String Orchestra, Chamber Orchestra and Symphony Orchestra will be performing under the direction of Dr. Christopher Campbell.

Featured on the program will be senior Elizabeth Nazeeri, playing the third movement of the Mendelssohn Violin Concerto. Chamber Orchestra will perform a Mozart Divertimento, String Orchestra has some Beauty and the Beast and La, La, Land, and the Symphony Orchestra will be performing Sleeping Beauty and Crown Imperial.
